<TD ALIGN="CENTER">
<H1>Exchange</H1>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</P>
<P>
T-LEX, which stands for Tokyo Lambda Exchange, is a layer-1/2/3 IX for
vairous academic or non-commercial networks. It is a brand new service
being established in March-June 2004 and it is operated by
<A HREF="http://www.wide.ad.jp/">WIDE Project</A> and terminates
the OC-192 circuit of <A HREF="http://www.ieeaf.org/">IEEAF</A>
TransPacific link in Tokyo side. This is a similar facility to
<A HREF="http://www.pacificwave.net/">The Pacific Wave</A> operated by
<A HREF="http://www.pnw-gigapop.net/">The Pacific Northwest Gigapop</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.washington.edu/">The University of Washington</A>,
and <A HREF="http://www.cenic.org/">CENIC</A>.
</P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="t-lex.png">
</P>

<P>
The current configuration internal to T-LEX is as follows:
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER">
<IMG SRC="t-lex-cfg-200508.png">
</P>

<P>
When T-LEX provides layer-3 service in IPv4 and in IPv6, it uses
AS23814.
</P>

